---
title: Mustard-Breaded Chicken Thighs with Brussels Sprouts and Sweet Potatoes
description: With this recipe, you can check another culinary feat off your list: you’ll be breading chicken the traditional way. We’ve got you prepped with a station for dipping and dredging the meat. Sure, it’s a multi-step process, but it’s easy and worth the effort. Plus, the sides are super simple: Brussels sprouts and sweet potatoes that require minimal attention.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mustard-breaded-chicken-thighs-family-1495d60b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mustard-breaded-chicken-thighs-family-32022eb8.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mustard-breaded-chicken-thighs-585805fcd4d92c49df0c06f2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 114 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 16 g
  sodium: 574 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{16%ounce} lengthwise. Toss with @olive oil{4%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} in a #medium bowl{}. Place on a #baking sheet{} cut-side down. Roast in oven until browned and crispy, about ~{25%minutes}.

Arrange 3 #plates{} in a row. Spread @flour{1%cup} on first plate. On the second, gently mix together half the @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, @water{2%TBSP}, and @Dijon mustard{2%TBSP}. On the last plate, mix together and spread out @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup}, @dried thyme{2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken thighs{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Working one at a time, toss in flour, coating all over. Shake off any excess. Dip in mustard mixture and coat evenly, letting excess drip off. Transfer to dish with panko, turning to cover all over in crumbs. Pat gently to adhere.

Transfer breaded chicken to a lightly-oiled baking sheet. @Dijon mustard{1%unit} for remaining. Bake in oven until chicken is cooked through and crumbs are a light gold color, ~{15-20%minutes}. Increase temperature to 450 degrees or place sheet under broiler. Continue baking (or broiling) until panko are golden brown, about ~{5%minutes}.

While chicken bakes, poke @sweet potatoes{24%ounce} all over with a #fork{}. Wrap each in a damp paper towel. Microwave on high for ~{10%minutes}. Remove from #microwave{} and place on baking sheet with chicken until meal is ready.

Cut an X in each sweet potato and dollop with remaining sour cream. Plate with Brussels sprouts and chicken.

> TIP: Line sheet with parchment to reduce sticking and for easy cleanup.